    "Following Miller (2019), we understand explanations as answers to contrastive 1 3 why-questions.",
    "We hold that the explanatory process comprises two distinct parts, social and abductive, that work in tandem to produce an understanding.",
    "In the second section, we apply this framework to medical practice.",
    "We argue that there is a good case to be made that medical explanations are abductive, which, alongside their social character, allows doctors to cross the TG above.",
    "We make this argument in spite of the fact that abductive reasoning remains underexplored within the relevant literature, which partially also motivates our present approach."
